The performance ratio (PR) is a parameter that indicates the overall efficiency of the system concerning the installed nominal power and the incident energy (Sharma et al. 2020; Belmahdi and El Bouardi 2020). This parameter is calculated as shown in Eq. 1, where Yf is the system performance and Yr is the reference performance.1PR=Yf/Yr\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$PR = Yf/Yr$$\end{document}

The solar fraction (SF) is the parameter that indicates whether the PV modules can supply the energy required by the load (Yahyaoui et al. 2015). This parameter is calculated as shown in Eq. 2, where E User is the energy supplied to the user and E Load is the user's energy requirement.2SF=EUser/ELoad\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$SF = E User/E Load$$\end{document}
